data.text: I agree with Bas, if a service needs components that belong to a different service (module), use core to get that service and ask for it's components.

Perhaps any one ServiceableComponent should be registered with a single service at most. This in order to keep modularity and a heap of other troubles. 
For example, what if two services want to call 'update' on this component at different rates? By locking this design we can avert future conflicts of interest.

I half agree: we already have a ValueAttribute and it's called Attribute<T>. For it to be able to hold pointers all we have to do is change that bloody RTTI_DEFINE_DATA() macro so it doesn't require a default destructor for type U where T = U*. Also we don't need an overflow of Attribute classes.

What we do need (and I think that is maybe what you mean with Pointer attribute?) is an attribute type that holds a path or pointer in a nap object tree to a certain object. ObjectAttribute or something.
